Aggregating 42,365.41 acres.
The reservation made by this order shall, as to all the above-described lands which are at this date legally appropriated under the public-land laws or reserved for any public purposes other than as a stock driveway, be subject to, and shall not interfere with or defeat, legal rights under such appropriations, or prevent the use for such public purposes of lands so reserved, so long as such appropriations are legally maintained or such reservations remain in force; and this reservation supersedes all existing withdrawals and reservations of the above-described lands for stock-driveway purposes.
FRANKLIN D ROOSEVELT
The White House,
July 17, 1937.
